1 (33) Targeted advertising. – Displaying advertisements to a consumer where the
2 advertisement is selected based on personal data obtained or inferred from that
3 consumer's activities over time and across nonaffiliated internet websites or
4 online applications to predict the consumer's preferences or interests.
5 "Targeted advertising" does not include any of the following:
6 a. Advertisements based on activities within a controller's own internet
7 websites or online applications.
8 b. Advertisements based on the context of a consumer's current search
9 query, visit to an internet website, or online application.
10 c. Advertisements directed to a consumer in direct response to the
11 consumer's request for information or feedback.
12 d. Processing personal data solely to measure or report advertising
13 frequency, performance, or reach.
14 (34) Third party. – With respect to personal data controlled by a controller, any
15 person other than the relevant consumer, the controller of the personal data,
16 or a processor or an affiliate of the processor or the controller.
17 (35) Trade secret. – As defined in Chapter 66, 95, or 113 of the General Statutes.
18 (36) Violent felony. – As defined in section 4201 of Title 11 and includes any
19 equivalent provision in the laws of any other state; the United States; any
20 territory, district, or subdivision of the United States; or any foreign
21 jurisdiction.
22 "§ 75F-103. Applicability of Chapter.
23 (a) This Chapter applies to persons that conduct business in the State or persons that
24 produce products or services that are targeted to residents of the State and that during the
25 preceding calendar year did any of the following:
26 (1) Controlled or processed the personal data of not less than 35,000 consumers,
27 excluding personal data controlled or processed solely for the purpose of
28 completing a payment transaction.
29 (2) Controlled or processed the personal data of not less than 10,000 consumers
30 and derived more than twenty percent (20%) of their gross revenue from the
31 sale of personal data.
32 (b) This Chapter does not apply to any of the following entities:
33 (1) Any regulatory, administrative, advisory, executive, appointive, legislative, or
34 judicial body of the State or a political subdivision of the State, including any
35 board, bureau, commission, or agency of the State or a political subdivision
36 of the State, but excluding any institution of higher education.
37 (2) Any financial institution or affiliate of a financial institution, all as defined in
38 15 U.S.C. § 6809, to the extent that the financial institution or affiliate is
39 subject to Title V of the Gramm Leach Bliley Act (15 U.S.C. § 6801, et seq.,
40 as amended) and the rules and implementing regulations promulgated
41 thereunder.
42 (c) This Chapter does not apply to the following information and data:
43 (1) Protected health information under HIPAA.
44 (2) Patient-identifying information for purposes of 42 U.S.C. § 290dd-2.
45 (3) Identifiable private information, as defined in 45 C.F.R. § 46.102, to the extent
46 that it is used for purposes of the federal policy for the protection of human
47 subjects pursuant to 45 C.F.R. § 46.
48 (4) Identifiable private information to the extent it is collected and used as part of
49 human subjects research pursuant to the ICH E6 Good Clinical Practice
50 Guideline issued by the International Council for Harmonisation of Technical
